{"content": "I need to multiply 509 \u00d7 573 in base 11.\n\n**Step 1: Convert 509 (base 11) to base 10**\n- 509\u2081\u2081 = 5\u00d711\u00b2 + 0\u00d711\u00b9 + 9\u00d711\u2070\n- = 5\u00d7121 + 0\u00d711 + 9\u00d71\n- = 605 + 0 + 9\n- = 614\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 2: Convert 573 (base 11) to base 10**\n- 573\u2081\u2081 = 5\u00d711\u00b2 + 7\u00d711\u00b9 + 3\u00d711\u2070\n- = 5\u00d7121 + 7\u00d711 + 3\u00d71\n- = 605 + 77 + 3\n- = 685\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 3: Multiply in base 10**\n- 614 \u00d7 685 = 420,590\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 4: Convert 420,590 back to base 11**\n- 420,590 \u00f7 11 = 38,235 R 5\n- 38,235 \u00f7 11 = 3,476 R 9\n- 3,476 \u00f7 11 = 316 R 0\n- 316 \u00f7 11 = 28 R 8\n- 28 \u00f7 11 = 2 R 6\n- 2 \u00f7 11 = 0 R 2\n\nReading remainders from bottom to top: 268095\n\n**Answer: 268095**", "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5", "prompt_tokens": 363, "completion_tokens": 396}